SGS Life Science Services Selects Oracle Corporation's Oracle Health Sciences LabPas to Accelerate Phase I Clinical Trial

Tuesday, 26 Jun 2012 07:59am EDT

SGS Life Science Services announced that it has selected Oracle Health Sciences LabPas to help accelerate subject recruitment, data capture and analysis, and improve workflows in Phase I trials. The organization will use Oracle Health Sciences LabPas delivered via the scalable and secure Oracle Health Sciences Cloud to automate Phase I clinical trial processes and to better integrate early-phase study data with its clinical data management system in order to expedite studies and improve insight. The project will be set up in SGS' Antwerp, Belgium, clinical unit.Â 

